  <title>Ethical Hacking</title>
  <offered>spring-odd</offered>
  <scheduleType>lecture</scheduleType>
  <catalogDescription>
    This course will cover how to identify different vulnerabilities from an attacker's point of view, what they might do with these vulnerabilities, and what measures you can take to mitigate these risks. Students will gain practical skills through red-team exercises and penetration labs.
      Cross-listed with SEC425. SEC525 students' grades will additionally depend either on participation in a research seminar project or the score from an approved certification exam (taken during the semester).
  </catalogDescription>
